    • Method Detail

      • initialBusinessId

        java.lang.String initialBusinessId()
        This delivers the initial business Id of a business object instance. A business Id is a unique identifier relevant in a business context such as a business process. The business Id may not be unique in a technical context such as the database table used to persist the business object.
        Returns:
        String value of the business Id + DBU._NS + initial technical Id (NEW_ID constant).

      • businessId

        java.lang.String businessId()
        This delivers the current business Id of a business object instance. A business Id is a unique identifier relevant in a business context such as a business process. The business Id may not be unique in a technical context such as the database table used to persist the business object. The business Id consists of a externally provided business id plus a technical id which is generally generated by the system in which the business object is persisted (ex. Database)
        Returns:
        String value of the current business Id + DUB._NS + current technical Id.

      • onlyBusinessId

        java.lang.String onlyBusinessId()
        This delivers the business Id without the technical Id part.
        Returns:
        String value of the current business Id + DUB._NS + current technical Id.
